{"article_id":"fh10xBFMN4d2U0Bg","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Story highlights","depth":2},{"id":1,"text":"Republicans confident","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"recall results signal","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"state will turn red in November","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"GOP certainly laid vital groundwork","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"that could put the state in play this fall","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"But Republicans are still working against historical forces in Wisconsin","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"Republicans scored a decisive victory Tuesday in the bitter Wisconsin recall election","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"as Gov . Scott Walker beat back Democratic challenger Tom Barrett and his organized labor allies","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"to keep his seat in Madison .","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"Unfortunately for a pundit class","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"that has been eager to ascribe sweeping national meaning to a race","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"that hinged entirely on local issues ,","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"the answer is ... maybe .","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"National GOP officials ,","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"eager to make hay out of the results ,","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"claim otherwise .","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"Walker :","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"'Time to move Wisconsin forward '","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"MUST WATCH Walker :","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"'Time to move Wisconsin forward '","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"02:29","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"Milwaukee mayor loses recall vote","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"Milwaukee mayor loses recall vote","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"02:33","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"`` It 's a lean-red state right now , ''","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"boasted Republican National Committee chairman Reince Priebus , a Kenosha native .","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"`` There is not a state in all of America","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"where Republicans know more about every voter than Wisconsin , ''","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"he told CNN .","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"`` And this was a message election about spending and debt and the size of government .","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"That will be the central question of November . ''","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"Republicans certainly laid vital groundwork","depth":8},{"id":38,"text":"that will put the state in play this fall","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"if Mitt Romney and his allies choose to spend money here , a likely prospect","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"considering","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"the Republican National Committee is chaired by a Wisconsinite .","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"Working hand-in-hand with the state Republican Party ,","depth":11},{"id":43,"text":"the RNC used the recall effort","depth":12},{"id":44,"text":"to identify four million potential voters , an invaluable achievement in a state","depth":13},{"id":45,"text":"where people do not register by party .","depth":13},{"id":46,"text":"Door-to-door canvassers used iPads , iPhones and iPods","depth":11},{"id":47,"text":"to feed voter information directly back to the RNC 's data center in Washington .","depth":11},{"id":48,"text":"The party also opened 24 volunteer centers statewide","depth":11},{"id":49,"text":"to assist in the Walker effort ,","depth":11},{"id":50,"text":"and all of those offices will be converted into presidential victory centers","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"beginning Wednesday .","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"The Obama campaign , meanwhile , has about 20 offices in Wisconsin ,","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"though its renowned field organizers have been on the ground for much longer , especially in Obama-friendly college towns and urban centers .","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"As for Romney , he mostly tiptoed around the recall fight like the president ,","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"declining to campaign in the state for Walker .","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"But the presumptive Republican presidential nominee is likely to make an appearance in the state soon ,","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"sources tell CNN .","depth":10},{"id":58,"text":"Romney tried to jump on Walker 's coattails late Tuesday with a congratulatory tweet ,","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"saying","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"the results `` will echo beyond the borders of Wisconsin . ''","depth":10},{"id":61,"text":"A range of national conservative groups , from the Karl Rove-backed American Crossroads to the Republican Governors Association to the Tea Party Patriots , seized on the outcome","depth":12},{"id":62,"text":"to proclaim victory over organized labor","depth":13},{"id":63,"text":"and tie the results to Obama 's re-election chances .","depth":13},{"id":64,"text":"`` This is a victory","depth":14},{"id":65,"text":"for keeping promises","depth":15},{"id":66,"text":"and delivering results for working families ,","depth":15},{"id":67,"text":"and a defeat for the broken politics of Barack Obama and big government unions , ''","depth":13},{"id":68,"text":"said American Crossroads president Steven Law .","depth":12},{"id":69,"text":"`` On to November ! ''","depth":11},{"id":70,"text":"To be sure ,","depth":14},{"id":71,"text":"Obama now faces a greater challenge in Wisconsin","depth":15},{"id":72,"text":"than he did in 2008 ,","depth":16},{"id":73,"text":"when he thumped John McCain here by 14 points .","depth":16},{"id":74,"text":"A recent poll from Marquette University Law School showed the president with a 49 % favorable rating in the state , a poor showing , but still better than Romney 's 40 % .","depth":13},{"id":75,"text":"The final result in Wisconsin come November may look more","depth":14},{"id":76,"text":"like it did in 2000 ,","depth":16},{"id":77,"text":"when Al Gore bested George W. Bush by 4,500 votes ,","depth":16},{"id":78,"text":"or 2004 ,","depth":16},{"id":79,"text":"when John Kerry beat Bush by 11,000 votes .","depth":16},{"id":80,"text":"`` Wisconsin has always been a battleground , ''","depth":15},{"id":81,"text":"said state Sen. Lena Taylor , a Democrat","depth":16},{"id":82,"text":"representing parts of Milwaukee .","depth":16},{"id":83,"text":"`` We are red with blue polka dots or blue with red polka dots .","depth":15},{"id":84,"text":"You really ca n't tell who has the majority","depth":16},{"id":85,"text":"because it flips","depth":17},{"id":86,"text":"and it changes all the time . ''","depth":17},{"id":87,"text":"But","depth":10},{"id":88,"text":"despite their mechanical advances and the base-energizing power of the recall ,","depth":12},{"id":89,"text":"Republicans are still working against historical forces in Wisconsin .","depth":12},{"id":90,"text":"The state has not voted for a Republican on the presidential level since 1984 .","depth":11},{"id":91,"text":"And","depth":10},{"id":92,"text":"if the GOP wants to use Tuesday 's election as an omen for November ,","depth":11},{"id":93,"text":"they ca n't ignore Obama 's strong showing in exit polls","depth":11},{"id":94,"text":"Even with turnout lower","depth":14},{"id":95,"text":"than it was in 2008","depth":14},{"id":96,"text":"-- and lower","depth":14},{"id":97,"text":"than it is expected to be this November --","depth":14},{"id":98,"text":"voters","depth":15},{"id":99,"text":"who participated in the recall","depth":15},{"id":100,"text":"told exit pollsters","depth":14},{"id":101,"text":"they preferred Obama to Romney by a 51-44 margin .","depth":13},{"id":102,"text":"Obama also bested Romney on questions","depth":12},{"id":103,"text":"of which candidate would do more","depth":13},{"id":104,"text":"to help the middle class","depth":14},{"id":105,"text":"and improve the economy .","depth":14},{"id":106,"text":"`` If Mitt Romney could n't beat the President among the electorate","depth":14},{"id":107,"text":"that turned out today","depth":15},{"id":108,"text":"to reelect Walker ,","depth":15},{"id":109,"text":"or with a spending gap","depth":14},{"id":110,"text":"that favored the GOP ,","depth":14},{"id":111,"text":"he faces an incredibly steep path in November , ''","depth":12},{"id":112,"text":"an Obama campaign official noted .","depth":11},{"id":113,"text":"Rank-and-file Republicans","depth":9},{"id":114,"text":"who volunteered for Walker in the race 's closing days","depth":9},{"id":115,"text":"differed","depth":8},{"id":116,"text":"on whether a recall win would translate to a Romney victory this fall .","depth":7},{"id":117,"text":"`` People are fired up ,","depth":9},{"id":118,"text":"and I think","depth":10},{"id":119,"text":"it 's going to make a huge difference , ''","depth":10},{"id":120,"text":"said Jeff Komp , an insurance broker from Erin Township","depth":10},{"id":121,"text":"who backed Walker .","depth":10},{"id":122,"text":"`` It 's going to carry forward","depth":10},{"id":123,"text":"and help the momentum in November . ''","depth":10},{"id":124,"text":"Jennifer Passig , a Walker supporter from Cedarburg","depth":10},{"id":125,"text":"who made get-out-the-vote phone calls for the governor ,","depth":10},{"id":126,"text":"had a different take .","depth":9},{"id":127,"text":"`` I think","depth":11},{"id":128,"text":"if Romney sticks the course","depth":12},{"id":129,"text":"he will have a lot of support here ,","depth":12},{"id":130,"text":"but I just do n't know","depth":12},{"id":131,"text":"if he will win the state , ''","depth":12},{"id":132,"text":"she said .","depth":11},{"id":133,"text":"`` We always seem to have Republican governors and Democratic governors .","depth":11},{"id":134,"text":"I do n't know why .","depth":11},{"id":135,"text":"It 's really strange . ''","depth":10},{"id":136,"text":"This weekend 's Wisconsin Democratic Convention in Appleton is certain to be consumed by hand-wringing and second-guessing about the recall , a grim prospect for one of the convention 's guest speakers :","depth":3},{"id":137,"text":"Democratic National Committee Chairman Debbie Wasserman Schultz ,","depth":4},{"id":138,"text":"who may face questions","depth":5},{"id":139,"text":"about why national Democrats did not do more","depth":6},{"id":140,"text":"to help Barrett .","depth":6},{"id":141,"text":"Democrats at Barrett 's election night headquarters searched for silver linings in the loss ,","depth":5},{"id":142,"text":"arguing","depth":6},{"id":143,"text":"that the recall race engaged their party 's base","depth":7},{"id":144,"text":"even as Democrats were outspent by Walker and outside conservative groups by a 7-1 margin .","depth":7},{"id":145,"text":"But others admitted","depth":5},{"id":146,"text":"that the loss was a painful blow for a party","depth":6},{"id":147,"text":"that was brimming with confidence just hours earlier .","depth":6},{"id":148,"text":"Mahlon Mitchell , a union leader","depth":7},{"id":149,"text":"who lost his bid for lieutenant governor on Tuesday ,","depth":7},{"id":150,"text":"acknowledged","depth":6},{"id":151,"text":"that Democrats have to find a way","depth":6},{"id":152,"text":"to re-energize their base after a bitter loss .","depth":6},{"id":153,"text":"`` I 'm not going to downplay now","depth":7},{"id":154,"text":"that we lost , ''","depth":7},{"id":155,"text":"Mitchell said .","depth":6},{"id":156,"text":"`` There 's no doubt","depth":8},{"id":157,"text":"this did have national ramifications ,","depth":8},{"id":158,"text":"but it shows","depth":8},{"id":159,"text":"we 've got an uphill battle .","depth":8},{"id":160,"text":"But this is not over by any means . ''","depth":6}],"relations":[{"parent":321,"left":296,"right":320,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":296,"left":0,"right":295,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":295,"left":176,"right":294,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":176,"left":166,"right":175,"rel